I loved this dish but made a couple of changes. First, I only used 1/2 stick butter (sorry Julia Child!). Then I added some crushed red chili peppers. I added about 1/8 cup of dry white wine at the end to add a bit of liquid. I also added some thinly sliced lemon wedges towards the end of the cooking time. They softened up and added a nice visual addition to the dish. I served the shrimp over white rice that I made with chicken broth and carmelized onions (a pilaf).This was super quick and easy to make. I will be making this again!

