Rating: 3
We just finished eating this. Delicous!! I took others' advice to use only 1 stick of butter and add 1/2 cup of white wine. Rather than using parsley, I used 2 tablespoons of fresh oregano, which I feel offers a stronger flavor that's delicious with butter and garlic. I baked the shrimp for 5 minutes before turning and then just another 3 after adding the lemon juice, zest, and oregano. One modification I would make next time is to reduce the amount of lemon juice. I found the flavor and tanginess a little overwhelming. By the way, I served this over brown rice that had been cooked in chicken broth with the zest of 1 lemon. I poured the sauce from the shrimp over the rice. Will make this again and again.

