Rating: 4
I gave this recipe a "4" because it was sooo easy and tasted absolutely WONDERFUL!! It was a "quick" night dinner. I had about 1 1/2 lbs of cooked shrimp - so I melted the butter (1/2 stick) and wine (1/2 cup)in the microwave. Then stired in the garlic and parsley. Marinated the shrimp until the rice was done and then cooked it for about 5 min. - Turned the shrimp and sprinkled it with the remaining parsley,zest and lemon juice. Baked it for about 7 minutes. It was to die for!!! You just have to watch the shrimp because it doesn't need to be "cooked", just warmed. Both my husband and son LOVED it!!!

